6|Indemnification Structures — Major expansion. Added tender-of-defense framework (5-step timeline with control backstop), conflict-of-interest carve-out, subrogation waiver, settlement control language (with capped-liability backstop for rejected settlements). Added three critical drafting decisions table (scope/defense control/cap interaction). Added regulatory flags table (CO SB 26-189 voiding indemnity for ADMT discrimination, CA Civil Code §1668, EU AI Act). Saffron-specific CO SB 26-189 compliance analysis. Expanded IDEAL/ACCEPTABLE/WALK-AWAY tiers with all new elements. Updated MSA §7.2 with AI-specific client indemnity (human oversight failure, regulated decisions, Thaler copyrightability claims). Updated MSA §7.3 with complete tender-of-defense procedure, subrogation waiver, settlement control, and cap-indemnity cross-reference. MSA version 1.3→1.4. Clause Genome version 1.6.0→1.7.0.